<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Counterfeit3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Counterfeit,</orth> vb. 1) to copy or imitate; a) absolutely: <cit><quote>--ing actors,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 3, 28</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou --est most lively,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 85</bibl></cit> (equivocally). -- b) trans.: <cit><quote>--ing the action of an old woman,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.121" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 121</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I c. him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.121" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 121</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 62</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.5" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.356" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 356</bibl>. Followed by an inf.: <cit><quote>--s to die with her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1776" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1776</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to feign, to forge; a) absolutely: <cit><quote>she doth but c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 107</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.167" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 167</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.167" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 167</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.167" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 167</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 22</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.114" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.65" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 6, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 64</bibl>. -- b) trans.: <cit><quote>c. sad looks,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.237" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 237</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 4, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.118" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 27</bibl>. <cit><quote>stamp and c. advantages,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.247" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 247</bibl></cit>. Followed by an inf.: <cit><quote>c. to swoon,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 17</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 28</bibl>. <cit><quote>c. to be a man,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.174" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 174</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>